    <div xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"><p>Here's my latest update to <a href="/tag/dhyana/">dhyana.pl</a>...</p>

<h2>Change Log</h2>

<ul>
<li>Added a title to the output image, which can be in a different font and colour from the rest of the text.</li>
<li>Use Getopt to parse command line, and accept more options.</li>
<li>Improved handling of certain dodgy <span class="caps">WMV </span>files, mostly thanks to Matt Pinkham.</li>
<li>Improved use of <span class="caps">FFMPEG</span></li>
<li>Code straightened out to use functions -- it used to be one big long mess.</li>
<li>Added a help function -- just run the program with the <tt>--help</tt> paramater.</li>
</ul>

<h2>Requirements</h2>

<ul>
<li>Perl Getopt::ArgvFile</li>
<li>Perl Getopt::Long â¥ 2.33</li>
<li>Perl Pod::Usage;</li>
<li>mplayer</li>
<li>ImageMagick</li>
</ul>

<h3>Optional</h3>

<ul>
<li>Perl File::chdir</li>
<li>Perl File::Spec</li>
<li>Perl Cwd</li>
<li><span class="caps">FFMPEG</span></li>
</ul>

<p>All of the Perl modules can be found in <a href="http://www.cpan.org"><span class="caps">CPAN</span></a>, here is the <a href="http://ffmpeg.mplayerhq.hu/"><span class="caps">FFMPEG</span></a> site and here is <a href="http://mplayerhq.hu/">mplayer</a>. And don't forget <a href="http://imagemagick.org">ImageMagick</a>.</p>

